g.text: 128th Brigade (2nd, 1/4th and 5th Battalions) withdrawn to concentration area, south of Ancona, under orders for Greece.
2/4th Battalion (28th Brigade) flown from Taranto, Italy landed on Hasani Airfield Athens under ELAS small arms and mortar fire.
2/4th Battalion engaged in street clearing operations against ELAS forces in Athens.
2/4th Bn garrison duties and relief work in Athens, Petramagaula & Khalkis.
2nd & 5th Bns disembarked at Piraeus from Italy.
‘Tigerforce’ (2nd & 5th Bns and 46th Div Recce Regt) occupy Argos & Naoplion in the Peloponnese to enforce the disbandment of ELAS forces.
1/4th Bn joined ‘Tigerforce’ in the Peloponnese from Italy.
2/4th Bn relief work in Petramagoula and Khalkis area.
128th Bde (2nd, 1/4th & 5th Bns) reorganised Civil Administration of Argolis – Korinthia Province of Peloponnese.
2/4th Bn moved to Crete from Greece and took prisoner over 12,000 Germans and 3,000 Italians who had surrendered.
